above all else, how to go with the flow. In brief episodes that tantalize and inspire, he takes us into the subtle complexities of human existence. Ultimately, Laozi, a master visionary, guides us to the mountaintop to reveal an expansive view of life.A marvelous edition of a timeless classic, this book also presents Laozi's original Chinese text in sidebars on each page, enriching the book for readers and students of Chinese without distracting from the English-language cartoons. The text is skillfully translated by Brian Bruya, who also provides an illuminating introduction.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aGraphic novels. 0aTaoism. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Taoist.2bisacsh  aAlan Watts.  aBook of the Tao and Its Virtue.  aBuddhism.  aCai Zhizhong.  aChinese philosophy.  aClassic of the Way’s Virtue.  aConfucianism.  aDaodejing.  aDaoist philosophy.  aDrunken Swordsman.  aLao Tzu.  aSima Qian.  aTao Ching.  aTao Te Ching.  aTao of Pooh.  aThe Path.  aTrying Not to Try.  aTsai Chih Chung.  aZhuangzi.  abestseller comics.  abestselling comics.  abilingual edition.  abooks by Tsai.  aclassical Chinese.  acomics.  aeastern philosophy.  afamous Asian cartoonists.  agifts for Chinese English readers.  agifts for students of Chinese.  aillustrated Chinese philosophy.  aintroduction to Daoism.  anonfiction comics.  aphilosophical comics.  aphilosophy comics.1 aBruya, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIyer, Pico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTsai, C. C., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z